<subSubSection pageId="108" pageNumber="386" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="108.[2071,2667,1790,2217]" pageId="108" pageNumber="386">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1908" box="[2072,2372,1873,1902]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nicaraguae">Peromyscus nicaraguae</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[2533,2665,1873,1902]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">mexicanus</taxonomicName>
species group. It was initially described as a distinct species but later placed in synon- omy with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[2205,2370,1987,2020]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">P. mexicanus</taxonomicName>
saxitilis. Recent DNA studies suggest that parts of what historically have been recognized as P. m. saxitilis should be considered as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1908" box="[2441,2622,2105,2138]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nicaraguae">P. nicaraguae</taxonomicName>
or P. salvadorensis. Two former subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[2072,2210,2188,2217]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nudipes">P. nudipes</taxonomicName>
(hesperus and 
<taxonomicName box="[2426,2541,2188,2217]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orientalis">orientalis</taxonomicName>
) should
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="108.[1458,2664,2227,2730]" box="[1459,2014,2227,2256]" pageId="108" pageNumber="386">
be assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. A. Allen" authorityYear="1908" box="[1667,1842,2227,2256]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nicaraguae">P. nicaraguae</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1459,2009,2263,2296]" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" type="distribution">
<caption box="[1459,2009,2263,2296]" inLine="true" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" targetBox="[1659,1663,2705,2730]" targetPageId="108">
<paragraph blockId="108.[1458,2664,2227,2730]" box="[1459,2009,2263,2296]" pageId="108" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1459,1635,2263,2296]" pageId="108" pageNumber="386">Distribution.</emphasis>
Honduras and Nicaragua.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="108" pageNumber="386" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="108.[1458,2664,2227,2730]" pageId="108" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1459,1709,2302,2335]" pageId="108" pageNumber="386">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
No information is yet available. The Nicaraguan Deermouse is presumably similar to the Mexican Deermouse (PF. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[2149,2287,2341,2374]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="108" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">mexicanus</taxonomicName>
), especially the subspecies formerly referred to as P. m. saxitilis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
